resources.description: These scripts download data from data.gov, load and link it into a relational database.
resources.name: dogdb database creation scripts

resources.description: This package includes synthesized ad-hoc queries for the dogdb databases.  Multiple queries, in linear, star, and circular join patterns are provided.  Eqivalent queries are presented in both SPARQL and SQL.  Unqualified queries (just table joins) and qualified queries (including an attribute value) are included.
resources.name: dogdb queries

organization.description: This organization is the repository for a large semi-synthetic, semantically rich dataset, modeled after the electronic medical record of a large medical institution. Using the highly diverse data.gov data repository and a multivariate data augmentation strategy, we can generate arbitrarily large semi-synthetic datasets which can be used to test new algorithms and computational platforms. The data is available both in relational (SQL) and semantic (RDF) forms.
organization.title: Semi-Synthetic Benchmark
organization.name: semi-synthetic-benchmark

name: dogdb-scripts-and-queries
notes: Data scripts and queries supporting the dogdb databases.  Scripts are included for downloading raw data from data.gov, building the SQL database tables and loading and linking the data.  SPARQL and SQL queries are also included.
title: dogdb-scripts-and-queries
